reviews.text: I tried it on 2014, don’t know if they hv improved the quality of food or not.  I had the world worst bibimbap in life there! (I tried bibimbap in Korea, Hk, and Korean town in L.A, New York, Sydney, Melbourne and brisbane, etc) I had very good experience over all and all the bibimbap I had in other places are up to standard

Excellent and rare outdoor space for BBQ. Good service and nice old Korean lady boss who runs the place. Food was also decent. Lots of options. Tried a ginseng tempura dipped in honey dish for the first time. The a la carte kalbi is tender and delicious. Highly recommended for groups to grill outside!
Decent Korean. Bit pricy though
Loved the service and food was yummy.

Pretty authentic Korean restaurant. We see a table of Korean people there for lunch. Their soy sauce crab is awesome, the best I had in HK, and best to eat it with rice. The bulgogi beef is great too, eat with lettuce and garlic. Overall the food quality is high and service is good.
